The article discusses how members of the United States Senate have a duty to protect the Constitution and secure the freedom to vote. However, they voted to preserve an old Senate rule instead of ensuring this fundamental freedom. The article mentions that anti-voter laws could make it harder for around 55 million Americans to vote, and this will impact every American. The administration is committed to fighting for federal legislation and changing Senate rules to protect the right to vote. They will also oppose anti-voter legislation pushed by Republican legislatures at the state level and support officials who work towards pro-voter legislation. The article concludes by stating that Americans have historically fought for the right to vote, and despite setbacks, they will continue to prevail.